verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Lead me, lead me, Savior,
lead me, lest I stray;
Gently down the stream of time,
Lead me, Savior, all the way.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Savior, lead me lest I stray,
Gently lead me all the way;
I am safe when by Thy side,
I would in Thy love abide.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Thou the refuge of my soul,
When life's stormy billows roll;
I am safe when Thou art nigh,
On Thy mercy I rely.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Savior, lead me, then at last,
When the storm of life is past;
I shall reach the land of day,
Where all tears are wiped away.{/lang-eng}
